  "text": "Vascular calcification is one of the common pathological changes of atherosclerosis and is an independent risk factor for cardiovascular disease. The incidence of vascular calcification increases with aging, smoking, hemodialysis, and diabetes mellitus. However, detailed molecular mechanisms of vascular calcification in diabetes mellitus remain poorly understood. In diabetes mellitus, high glucose promotes trans-differentiation of vascular smooth muscle cells, which is thought to cause vascular calcification, and hyperinsulinemia and elevated advanced glycosylation end products may play a role in vascular calcification [CITATION_1] .",
